/span>)</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hg</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Eventually\">∀ᵐ</a> (<span class=\"fn\">a</span> : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>) <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Eventually\">∂</a><span class=\"fn\">μa</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Eventually\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Map.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.map\">Measure.map</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">g</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">μc</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">μd</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Dynamics/Ergodic/MeasurePreserving.html#MeasureTheory.MeasurePreserving\">MeasurePreserving</a> <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">p</span> : <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <span class=\"fn\">γ</span>) =&gt; <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod.mk\">(</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span>.1</span></span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod.mk\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">g</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span>.1</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span>.2</span></span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod.mk\">)</a>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">μa</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Prod.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.prod\">prod</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">μc</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">μb</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Prod.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.prod\">prod</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">μd</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Let `f : α → β` be a measure-preserving map.\nFor a.e. all `a`, let `g a : γ → δ` be a measure-preserving map.\nAlso suppose that `g` is measurable as a function of two arguments.\nThen the map `fun (a, c) ↦ (f a, g a c)` is a measure-preserving map\nfor the product measures on `α × γ` and `β × δ`.\n\nSome authors call a map of the form `fun (a, c) ↦ (f a, g a c)` a *skew product* over `f`,\nthus the choice of a name.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Prod.html#MeasureTheory.MeasurePreserving.skew_product","kind":"theorem","line":857,"name":"MeasureTheory.MeasurePreserving.skew_product","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Prod.lean#L857-L886"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Prod.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.prod_smul_left\"><span class=\"name\">MeasureTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Measure</span>.<span class=\"name\">prod_smul_left</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">β</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSpace\">MeasurableSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSpace\">MeasurableSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span 