ble\">Measurable</a> <span class=\"fn\">fun (<span class=\"fn\">y</span> : <span class=\"fn\">β</span>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">μ</span> (<span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>) =&gt; <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod.mk\">(</a><span class=\"fn\">x</span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod.mk\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\">y</span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod.mk\">)</a>)</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Operations.html#Set.preimage\">⁻¹'</a> <span class=\"fn\">s</span>)</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `μ` is an s-finite measure, and `s ⊆ α × β` is measurable, then `y ↦ μ { x | (x, y) ∈ s }` is\na measurable function. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Prod.html#measurable_measure_prodMk_right","kind":"theorem","line":103,"name":"measurable_measure_prodMk_right","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Prod.lean#L103-L107"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Prod.html#measurable_measure_prodMk_left\"><span class=\"name\">measurable_measure_prodMk_left</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">β</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSpace\">MeasurableSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSpace\">MeasurableSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">ν</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.Measure\">MeasureTheory.Measure</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Typeclasses/SFinite.html#MeasureTheory.SFinite\">MeasureTheory.SFinite</a> <span class=\"fn\">ν</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> (<span class=\"fn\">α</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span>)</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hs</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSet\">MeasurableSet</a> <span class=\"fn\">s</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#Measurable\">Measurable</a> <span class=\"fn\">fun (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">ν</span> (<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod.mk\">Prod.mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Operations.html#Set.preimage\">⁻¹'</a> <span class=\"fn\">s</span>)</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `ν` is an s-finite measure, and `s ⊆ α × β` is measurable, then `x ↦ ν { y | (x, y) ∈ s }`\nis a measurable function.\n\nNot true without the s-finite assumption: on `ℝ × ℝ` with the product sigma-algebra, let `s` be the\ndiagonal and let `ν` be an uncountable sum of Dirac measures (all Dirac measures for points in a\nset `t`). Then `ν (Prod.mk x ⁻¹' s) = ν {x} = if x ∈ t then 1 else 0`. If `t` is chosen\nnon-measurable, this will not be measurable. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Prod.html#measurable_measure_prodMk_left","kind":"theorem","line":90,"name":"measurable_measure_prodMk_left","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Prod.lean#L90-L101"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Prod.html#measurable_measure_prodMk_left_finite\"><span class=\"name\">measurable_measure_prodMk_left_finite</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">β</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSpace\">MeasurableSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSpace\">MeasurableSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">ν</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.Measure\">MeasureTheory.Measure</a> <span class=\"f